Questions:
   1. Which is the smallest deployable unit of execution in Kubernetes?
      The Pod is the smallest deployable unit in Kubernetes. 
      A Pod encapsulates one or more containers, their storage, and networking resources,
      and represents a single instance of a running process in the cluster.
   2. Which controller creates a load balancer in the cloud infrastructure?
     The Service of type LoadBalancer is managed by the cloud-controller-manager.
     This controller interacts with the underlying cloud provider‚Äôs APIs to provision 
     and configure an external load balancer that routes traffic to the Kubernetes Service.


D∆∞·ªõi ƒë√¢y l√† c√°c controller c·ªët l√µi ch√≠nh:
  1.	Deployment Controller
  2.	ReplicaSet Controller
  3.	StatefulSet Controller
  4.	DaemonSet Controller
  5.	Job Controller
  6.	CronJob Controller
  7.	Namespace Controller
  8.	Service Controller (T·∫°o Load Balancer trong cloud)
  9.	EndpointSlice/Endpoint Controller
  10.	Node Controller
  11.	PersistentVolume Controller
  12.	Replication Controller (C≈©, h·∫ßu nh∆∞ ƒë∆∞·ª£c thay th·∫ø b·ªüi ReplicaSet)
  13.	ResourceQuota Controller
  14.	ServiceAccount Controller
  15.	Garbage Collector (GC) Controller
  16.	TTL-After-Finished Controller


CHAPTER 2 Installing Kubernetes
    Structure
      In this chapter, we will cover the following topics:
      Basic Tools
      Minikube:
       - One of the easiest ways to set up a local Kubernetes cluster is by using Minikube
       - It works on Linux, MacOS, and Windows.
       - The main highlights of Minikube are its ability to be deployed on VMs, containers, and even on bare-metal.
       - When it comes to deploying on containers, it supports CRI-O, Docker, and containerd.
       - Minikube also supports advanced features such as LoadBalancer, filesystem mounts, FeatureGates, and NetworkPolicy.
       - Since we have got Oracle VirtualBox and Vagrant setup done,
         we will launch Ubuntu 22.04 using Vagrant and then set up Minikube on it.
         Minikube supports containers, so we will use Docker to launch a singlenode Kubernetes cluster.
      Microk8s
      KIND - Kubernetes INside Docker
      Kubeadm
      OS: Ubuntu 22.04

      Questions: 
